              <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">Your portfolio: 24 thumbnail photos, click to enlarge, that's it. Competitor: full-screen project galleries, before/after sliders, client testimonials, narrative flow explaining design decisions. Visit duration: 47 seconds vs 3:12. People invest in stories, not photo dumps. Your best work deserves a narrative. Tell the story of each project: challenge, solution, result.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-red-400 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-white text-lg">No project narratives = invisible expertise</p>
              <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">Beautiful photos without context = visual only. "Why did you choose that material?" "How did you solve the site constraints?" "What sustainability features did you integrate?" Narratives show thinking process, problem-solving, expertise. Clients hire architects for their minds, not just their photos. Show your thinking.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-red-400 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-white text-lg">No client testimonials = no social proof</p>
              <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">Your site has gorgeous photos. Competitor has gorgeous photos PLUS 12 client testimonials: "Marcus listened to how we LIVE, not just what we wanted," "Our home won 2023 NARI Design Award," "Budget came in 3% under estimate." Photos show capability. Testimonials show collaboration, reliability, results. Which would you hire?</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-red-400 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-white text-lg">No process explanation = confused clients</p>
              <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">Phone calls: "How long does this take?" "What's the process?" "What are the phases?" All answerable on site. Add process page: discovery → schematic design → design development → construction docs → construction administration with typical timelines (6-12 months residential). Process visible = informed clients = smoother calls. Marcus reduced discovery call duration 47% with process page.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-red-400 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-white text-lg">No transparent pricing = lost opportunities</p>
              <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">"Contact for pricing" loses qualified clients to transparent architects. Show fee structure: "$150-250/hour for design phases, 10-15% of construction cost for full services." Clients budget for architecture. Hidden pricing = anxiety = bounce. Transparent pricing = trust = commitment. Your fees aren't secret. Your competitor's are visible.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-red-400 font-black text-2xl flex-shrink-0">✗</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-white text-lg">Heavy 3MB photos = PageSpeed 48 = 67% bounce rate</p>
              <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mt-1">Gorgeous 3MB photos. PageSpeed 48. Mobile load: 12 seconds. Bounce rate 67%. Beautiful photos that don't load = no photos at all. Compress to 200KB, lazy loading, proper sizing. PageSpeed 96, mobile load 2 seconds, bounce 23%. Mobile is 67% of traffic. Optimize or lose.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- UNEXPECTED FINDINGS: ARCHITECT EDITION -->
  <section class="py-12 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-amber-50">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="bg-white border-[3px] border-orange-300 p-6 md:p-8 my-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-black text-gray-900 mb-2">Unexpected Findings After 35 Hours</h2>
        <p class="text-xs text-gray-500 mb-6 uppercase tracking-wider font-black">Data nobody tells architects</p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Grid vs full-screen galleries: 4x visit duration, 3x inquiries</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Architect portfolio: thumbnail grid, 47-second average visit. Rebuilt with Framer: full-screen project galleries, before/after sliders, client testimonials, narrative flow. Visit duration: 3:12 (4x longer). Inquiries: 3/month to 9/month (3x increase). People invest in stories, not photos.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">$2.4M project lost to architect with "worse" work - portfolio was difference</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Architect with superior work lost $2.4M commission. Client showed both sites: his basic grid vs competitor's Framer site with full-screen galleries, project narratives. Client: "Your work is better, but his portfolio shows he understands presentation." Presentation = perceived quality.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">3MB photos → 200KB: PageSpeed 48→96, bounce 67%→23%</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Gorgeous 3MB photos. PageSpeed 48. Mobile: 12-second load. Bounce 67%. Compressed to 200KB, lazy loading: PageSpeed 96, mobile load 2 seconds, bounce 23%. Beautiful photos that don't load = no photos at all. Optimize or lose on mobile.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">"Projects" vs categorized sections: 47% more qualified leads</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Architect lumped all projects together. Split into Residential, Commercial, Interior, Landscape. Navigation: clear, specific. Qualified inquiries: +47%. Clients know exactly what you do. Make it obvious who your work is for.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Process page visible: 47% shorter discovery calls</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Added process page with phases, timelines, typical deliverables. Discovery call duration: -47%. Clients understand process before calling. Questions shift from "how does this work?" to "when can we start?" Better qualified leads.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-orange-600 font-black text-xl flex-shrink-0">!</span>
            <div>
              <p class="font-black text-gray-900">Client testimonials visible: 62% more qualified leads</p>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-1">Added 12 client testimonials with photos, specific results. Qualified leads: 45%→73% (+62%). Photos show capability. Testimonials show collaboration, reliability, results. Both needed. Social proof converts.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

